CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1782366482
OL,3,CWhat happens with 33C heat hits the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FThe advice is particularly important
OL,7,Ffor people living with dementia, who
OL,8,Fmay be less aware of the effects of
OL,9,Fhot weather or less likely to
OL,10,Frecognise the signs of dehydration.
OL,12,FHealth experts are encouraging people
OL,13,Fto check on elderly relatives,
OL,14,Fneighbours and vulnerable friends
OL,15,Fduring the heatwave, especially those
OL,16,Fwho live alone.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,363,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1782366482
OL,3,CWhat happens with 33C heat hits the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FSimple measures such as drinking
OL,7,Fplenty of water, keeping homes cool by
OL,8,Fclosing curtains during the hottest
OL,9,Fparts of the day, avoiding strenuous
OL,10,Factivity in the afternoon sun and
OL,11,Fseeking shade where possible can
OL,12,Fsignificantly reduce the risk of heat
OL,13,Fexhaustion and heatstroke.
OL,15,FWith temperatures expected to remain
OL,16,Fhigh throughout the week, emergency
OL,17,Fservices are urging residents to enjoy
OL,18,Fthe sunshine responsibly and take
OL,19,Fsensible precautions to stay safe.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
