OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,363,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1782366482
OL,3,CWhat happens with 33C heat hits the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FFire crews are also among those urging
OL,7,Fresidents to take extra care as the
OL,8,Fprolonged dry conditions increase the
OL,9,Frisk of grass, woodland and moorland
OL,10,Ffires.
OL,12,FLancashire Fire and Rescue Service
OL,13,Fsays seemingly harmless activities
OL,14,Fsuch as barbecues can quickly lead to
OL,15,Fserious incidents during periods of
OL,16,Fextreme heat.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,363,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1782366482
OL,3,CWhat happens with 33C heat hits the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FLiam Wilson, Head of Prevention at
OL,7,FLancashire Fire and Rescue Service,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Barbecues can pose particular
OL,9,Frisks and can be extremely dangerous
OL,10,Fin this environment and that is
OL,11,Fbecause of the potential of easy and
OL,12,Frapid fire development out in open
OL,13,Fspaces where it is extremely
OL,14,Fchallenging for us to contain the fire
OL,15,Fand secondly, extinguish it.
OL,26,@pD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,363,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1782366482
OL,3,CWhat happens with 33C heat hits the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,F"If you are looking to enjoy the
OL,7,Fcountryside, take a packed lunch, take
OL,8,Fa prepared meal, please don't risk, in
OL,9,Fthese particular weather conditions,
OL,10,Fthe potential of igniting any sort of
OL,11,Ffire.
OL,13,F"That is because when they do ignite,
OL,14,Fthey spread so rapidly that it is
OL,15,Fextremely challenging for us and that
OL,16,Fthen impacts on our ability to respond
OL,17,Fto critical incidents elsewhere."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
